svg.title: Digital Art Frame 3
svg.desc:
Digital Art Frame 3 V3 - Added ability to remove frame by passing f=0 in the query string of the url If the frame is not displayed, the credits are not display either Added ability to remove credits by passing c=0 in the query string of the url - not required if f=0 is passed. Can turn credits on by adding c=1 after f=0 i.e. ?f=0&c=1 Added the ability to bypass 1 second delay required for upload to openclipart by adding d=0 to the query string of the url Added keyboard navigation: right arrow - advance, left arrow - go back, down arrow - pause Clicking on right, left, and bottom of image provides same navigation with or without frame displayed V2 - Added support for colored backgrounds and limit the number of images by appending bg=black and/or a=number to the url query string. Fixed an issue with only passing an uploader without a query string Pass a query string to the SVG image of the form: ?q=query&u=user&s=sort&t=timeout where query is an Openclipart query search, user is a specific uploader, sort is one of (date,favorites,downloads) and timeout is the time in seconds to display image any or all of the query parameters need not be passed. Embed in a web page by copying the SVG code and placing it in a div with an aspect ratio of 16:9, i.e.
insert SVG image code here then comment out or delete meta tags above Might also want to change the "load" event listener and comment out or delete the Titleframe needed for uploading to openclipart Change change the displayCredits variable to false to remove credits displayed on frame, Change the default query, and adjust the timeout variable
